from.body:
Hi. In a nutshell.

In the exchanges we find young forks (the ones that can be mined), analyze their infrastructure. Where servers, nodes, capitalization.
Find a place where crypto holders communicate (discord, etc).
Learn the IP of the nodes. Most likely it will be IPv6. Let's start snooping. Hop into chat room, found earlier and write that there is a problem, crypto is not output, operations are not performed. (since crypto depends on mining, there will indeed be problems).
Holders become nervous and withdraw the main balance. Crypto drops in value. We buy at a low price. We let go of the ddos. Crypt goes up again. We come out in the black. Or the option of writing to the creators about the possibility of a buyback if they want the ddos to end. From the main problematic points is the implementation of Ipv6 ddos.
